  question: Why are visual components placed in a child game object separated from
    logic components in this lecture?
  optionList:
  - To reduce memory usage
  - To keep the game objects organized
  - To improve graphics rendering
  - To improve performance
  correctOptionIndex: 1
  answer: Separating visuals from logic keeps the parent game object clean and organized,
